Flooding Kills 57 People in 3 Chinese Provinces in September

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-09-20T00:22:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/flooding-kills-57-people-in-3-chinese-provinces-in-september.html
Flooding triggered by heavy rains
in September killed 57 people in three Chinese provinces, the
Ministry of Civil Affairs said in a statement on its website
yesterday.  The flooding affected 12.3 million people and 650,666
hectares of crops in the provinces of Sichuan, Shaanxi and
Henan, the statement said. Direct economic losses were 17.3
billion yuan, according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  